comments.text:
It's interesting how you "devalued" your work by charging 2K-5K per month, when actually you deliver the same output as if they were to hire a regular custom software development company. But that software development company would charge them 5x for the same work and companies would be okay to pay that, just because they are used to.

Considering that you're already established in this space, you should charge way more for monthly subscription. 
Especially because you're a consultant and you help them design processes, as most companies suck at that.
comments.author: @tihomirtika4686

comments.text: We charge upwards of 5k a month, depending on the need of the company. In our experience that results in a good ROI for our agency and client retention, I don't see how I "devalued" my work. Charging 5x that for a minimum of 25k+/Mo would significantly limit the amount of companies we can work with.
comments.author: @BenAI92

comments.text:
@BenAI92  You devalued your work in comparison to what would charge them other custom software development companies. (And I don't see a good reason why would you do that, when the output you give them is often better). Bigger companies that already have some custom solutions in their companies are used to paying much more to IT companies for building that.

And Yes, and you should limit the amount of companies you work with as you're on that level now. 
I believe you should work with companies that are at least 50+ employees and not 10+.

In that way, you will be able to charge them more for the same work. 
Based on this video, you seem to be focused on hitting a certain number of clients (which IMO will eventually affect your profit margins as you will always have to hire more people in order to deliver the quality of work)

Anyway, it's your business, not mine, I just thought to share some outside perspective :)
